00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:31,600
 but I was catching, I must hurry,

518
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:33,120
 but the Holy Spirit did this.

519
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:39,520
 And I just look at her, and she was those homeless,

520
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:42,280
 she was a homeless lady with all these plastic bags,

521
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,860
 with her, and I was like, should I just go?

522
00:22:47,860 --> 00:22:51,820
 But the Holy Spirit made me look at her,

523
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:55,300
 how can you just turn away and walk away?

524
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:57,780
 So I went to her and I just say,

525
00:22:57,780 --> 00:22:59,940
 hi, have you had dinner?

526
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:02,540
 And she, out of all her plastic bags,

527
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:06,140
 she took out this one of these like lunch boxes,

528
00:23:06,140 --> 00:23:08,660
 and actually it's whatever is inside, I forgot,

529
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:10,820
 but it stinks a little bit that I remember,

530
00:23:11,860 --> 00:23:13,780
 and I said, is this your dinner?

531
00:23:13,780 --> 00:23:17,540
 It's 1 a.m., and she said, yeah, this is my food,

532
00:23:17,540 --> 00:23:21,740
 I'm like, no way, and we were near Wan Chai MTR,

533
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:24,860
 so I just went to the MTR and I was just,

534
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:27,380
 I just said, hey, can I get you something from McDonald's?

535
00:23:27,380 --> 00:23:29,180
 And I said, hey, actually, I'm so hungry right now,

536
00:23:29,180 --> 00:23:30,540
 I wanna go to McDonald's and grab something,

537
00:23:30,540 --> 00:23:33,300
 would you like, can I get you something?

538
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:35,500
 She said, yeah, fish, you know, fish au filet,

539
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:37,220
 I said, okay, just wait for me here.

540
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:40,180
 So I went to McDonald's, grabbed whatever,

541
00:23:40,180 --> 00:23:43,180
 and then I came back, and I wanted to have a chat with her,

542
00:23:43,180 --> 00:23:45,860
 and then she ran away.

543
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:50,620
 But there was another time I was in Mong Kok,

544
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:54,180
 you know, Mong Kok, if you ever took the bus to Mong Kok,

545
00:23:54,180 --> 00:23:58,860
 I was on the side where it used to be this pedestrian area,

546
00:23:58,860 --> 00:24:01,100
 but if you wanna take the bus back to Yuen Long,

547
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:03,380
 a lot of you, you look like you never took a bus

548
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:04,380
 from Mong Kok to Yuen Long,

549
00:24:04,380 --> 00:24:06,340
 but you have to cross the main road,

550
00:24:06,340 --> 00:24:08,660
 the Nathan Road, to the other side and come back,

551
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:11,740
 so you either cross, you know, traffic light,

552
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:15,820
 or you go through that tunnel, that subway,

553
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:17,380
 so, oh, somebody nodded, okay.

554
00:24:17,380 --> 00:24:20,580
 So there's one time I just walk through that tunnel,

555
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:23,300
 and then again, I saw these two men here,

556
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,780
 it's late in the night, 11 something,

557
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:26,820
 and they were having, like, two men sharing, like,

558
00:24:26,820 --> 00:24:29,220
 a box of rice or something.

559
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:31,780
 I was walking, I'm like, man, it's late,

560
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:33,860
 my wife is waiting for me, she will be angry

561
00:24:33,860 --> 00:24:35,020
 if I don't go home.

562
00:24:35,020 --> 00:24:37,940
 She's, oh, she's here, okay.

563
00:24:37,940 --> 00:24:41,300
 I thought she was, anyway, and then I have that, like,

564
00:24:41,300 --> 00:24:45,540
 hey, hey, hey, look, so I turn around and look.

565
00:24:45,540 --> 00:24:48,180
 Okay, I walk back, and I ask them,

566
00:24:48,180 --> 00:24:52,340
 so, the two of you are sharing, like,

567
00:24:52,340 --> 00:24:55,820
 one, like, lunchbox, is that enough for you?

568
00:24:55,820 --> 00:24:58,380
 Can I get you something, what would you like to eat?

569
00:24:58,380 --> 00:25:00,780
 So one guy just randomly said, oh, he wanted this or that,

570
00:25:00,780 --> 00:25:02,820
 but that was late, in Hong Kong, you know,

571
00:25:02,820 --> 00:25:05,940
 nowadays, past 10 p.m., there's nothing out there,

572
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:07,180
 except maybe one or two stores.

573
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:09,740
 So I went up the other side of the tunnel,

574
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:12,260
 found this restaurant that is still open,

575
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:13,740
 and got some, like, (speaks in foreign language)

576
00:25:13,740 --> 00:25:16,380
 I don't even know how, oh, chicken feet rice, yes.

577
00:25:16,380 --> 00:25:18,380
 And I brought back to the tunnel,

578
00:25:18,380 --> 00:25:19,660
 and they were, like, just enjoying,

579
00:25:19,660 --> 00:25:22,700
 and so, you know, as Christians, we wanna talk, right?

580
00:25:22,700 --> 00:25:27,700
 So I'm like, so, I just wanna tell you Jesus love you,

581
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:31,700
 you know, and to my surprise, one of the guys,

582
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,700
 you know, he was homeless, but he lives in,

583
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:36,980
 under tunnel, you know, that, and he just picked up,

584
00:25:36,980 --> 00:25:39,380
 just pulled out a Bible from all his stash,

585
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:42,300
 and said, oh, you know what, I always have a question here

586
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,780
 that I don't really understand.

587
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:45,460
 (audience laughs)

588
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:49,980
 And that random dinner turned into a Bible study

589
00:25:49,980 --> 00:25:52,340
 in that tunnel in Mong Kok.

590
00:25:52,340 --> 00:25:57,700
 I don't get that every time, but sometimes,

591
00:25:57,700 --> 00:26:00,740
 if I put service before sermon, if I try,

592
00:26:00,740 --> 00:26:04,700
 if I become, try to become a church in action,

593
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:08,580
 I know sometimes I still earn the right to be heard,

594
00:26:08,580 --> 00:26:11,420
 that I could still share the message with them.

595
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:16,100
 The Church of Jesus has to be a church in action.

596
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:20,140
 We need to have our services before our sermons.

597
00:26:20,140 --> 00:26:23,460
 We need to serve before we try to speak into people's life.

598
00:26:23,460 --> 00:26:29,060
 Wait, where am I, sorry, brain's not working.

599
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:33,340
 You know the most beautiful thing that day

600
00:26:33,340 --> 00:26:37,340
 when Peter pulled that guy up from the ground,

601
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:39,540
 and he was jumping and leaping, you know,

602
00:26:39,540 --> 00:26:42,340
 the Bible says he followed Peter and John,

603
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:46,300
 jump, jump, jump into the place of worship,

604
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:49,380
 'cause now he's whole, he's healed, he's shalom,

605
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:51,780
 he can be in the presence of God.

606
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:54,140
 The thing is not just about his physical healing.

607
00:26:54,140 --> 00:26:57,420
 Now, from an outsider, because of that miracle,

608
00:26:57,420 --> 00:27:01,460
 he was brought into the presence of God, he was accepted.

609
00:27:01,460 --> 00:27:03,460
 He didn't just experience a miracle

610
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:05,940
 that he could go and play football now,

611
00:27:05,940 --> 00:27:08,780
 but he received a miracle that now he can know

612
00:27:08,780 --> 00:27:11,780
 I'm truly a son of God, that I'm accepted,

613
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:14,340
 that I could be in the presence of God,

614
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:18,260
 I can come and worship him, I can join, I belong.

615
00:27:18,260 --> 00:27:20,020
 That's the miracle he received,

616
00:27:20,020 --> 00:27:22,460
 and today, here in Hong Kong,

617
00:27:22,460 --> 00:27:24,860
 who are the people who are so marginalized?

618
00:27:24,860 --> 00:27:26,820
 Who are the people who are so rejected?

619
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:29,260
 Who are the ones who need to be accepted

620
00:27:29,260 --> 00:27:30,980
 into the presence of God to know

621
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:33,900
 that they are cherished, to know that they have a place here?

622
00:27:33,900 --> 00:27:35,460
 Who are those people?

623
00:27:35,460 --> 00:27:38,020
 But more importantly, who will be the ones

624
00:27:38,020 --> 00:27:41,260
 who go to them to serve them?

625
00:27:41,260 --> 00:27:43,340
 Even before we speak anything,

626
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:45,660
 we bring any message, any sermon to them,

627
00:27:45,660 --> 00:27:48,580
 who would be those people?

628
00:27:48,580 --> 00:27:51,420
 That's my question for all of us.

629
00:27:51,420 --> 00:27:56,180
 And I just wanna, I just wanna say,

630
00:27:57,460 --> 00:28:00,980
 this story is such a powerful reminder

631
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:03,580
 of what happened when the church in action

632
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:08,140
 responds to the need with the power of Jesus' name.

633
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:09,900
 It's more than just physical healing,

634
00:28:09,900 --> 00:28:12,660
 it's a radical transformation of this man,

635
00:28:12,660 --> 00:28:16,620
 and also the acceptance into God's presence.

636
00:28:16,620 --> 00:28:20,100
 And like I ask, where are these people in our city right now?

637
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:23,020
 Where are these people in Yuen Long right now

638
00:28:23,020 --> 00:28:26,580
 that we can engage with, that we can touch their hearts,

639
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:30,700
 not just with a donation, although that's also very good,

640
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:34,820
 but who are these people that we can engage with

641
00:28:34,820 --> 00:28:38,100
 through the power, the transformative power of Jesus?

642
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:43,460
 When I planned this whole sermon, like last week,

643
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:44,940
 I was supposed to end here,

644
00:28:44,940 --> 00:28:51,220
 'cause you know, sometimes, if I'm just honest,

645
00:28:51,220 --> 00:28:54,500
 it's easier to preach a principle than a miracle.

646
00:28:54,500 --> 00:28:55,860
 You get what I mean?

647
00:28:55,860 --> 00:28:58,420
 It's easier to preach a principle than to preach a miracle,

648
00:28:58,420 --> 00:29:02,340
 because I tell you some principles, you go do ABC,

649
00:29:02,340 --> 00:29:05,340
 that's all what we're going out to do, that's easy.

650
00:29:05,340 --> 00:29:08,260
 If I'm telling you God is calling us to go out there

651
00:29:08,260 --> 00:29:10,460
 to perform these miracles, you're like,

652
00:29:10,460 --> 00:29:13,020
 I'm not so sure about it, and next week you come back,

653
00:29:13,020 --> 00:29:16,820
 maybe two or three of you would maybe try it,

654
00:29:16,820 --> 00:29:19,220
 and then, but you fail, and maybe, I don't know.

655
00:29:19,220 --> 00:29:22,300
 But I've prayed for people before and nothing happened.

656
00:29:22,300 --> 00:29:23,620
 I experienced that.

657
00:29:23,620 --> 00:29:25,700
 I went to talk to people and they run away before.

658
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:26,700
 I experienced that.

659
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:30,220
 So if I'm telling you to go out and do all these miracles,

660
00:29:30,220 --> 00:29:32,700
 maybe you would try, but maybe nothing would happen,

661
00:29:32,700 --> 00:29:34,860
 and you would come back very disappointed,

662
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:36,940
 and I would look like, oh, like,

663
00:29:36,940 --> 00:29:38,380
 in Cantonese, (speaking in foreign language)

664
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:40,780
 like, I'll be, you know.

665
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:44,020
 I'm like, God, maybe, you know, I'll just stop

666
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:46,700
 at all these very nice principle, you know,

667
00:29:46,700 --> 00:29:48,260
 we go and serve and all that.

668
00:29:48,260 --> 00:29:51,860
 But then yesterday, at the last day of the conference,

669
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:55,420
 in the morning, the speaker gave a message.

670
00:29:55,420 --> 00:29:59,460
 He said, you know, God, when God calls people,

671
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:02,500
 he always calls them to do the impossible.

672
00:30:02,500 --> 00:30:04,460
 Because if God calls you to do the possible,

673
00:30:04,460 --> 00:30:07,940
 then, then you can just do it by yourself.

674
00:30:07,940 --> 00:30:09,180
 All the stuff that I tell you,

675
00:30:09,180 --> 00:30:11,100
 go and, you know, find someone under the tunnel

676
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:12,020
 and go and talk to them,

677
00:30:12,020 --> 00:30:13,820
 these are all the things you can do.

678
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:16,740
 And with you, yeah, okay, I have done it,

679
00:30:16,740 --> 00:30:19,500
 but God always calls us to do the impossible.

680
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:21,860
 God has empowered John and Peter,

681
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:23,820
 the entire early church, to do something

682
00:30:23,820 --> 00:30:25,780
 that is impossible.

683
00:30:25,780 --> 00:30:28,420
 If that is possible, then we would tend

684
00:30:28,420 --> 00:30:29,860
 to rely on our own strength.

685
00:30:29,860 --> 00:30:32,300
 But if God calls us to do something

686
00:30:32,300 --> 00:30:34,700
 that is so difficult, that is so big,

687
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:39,380
 so beyond ourselves, that we know we have to rely on him.

688
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,580
 But if we look at stories in the Bible

689
00:30:41,580 --> 00:30:44,620
 about all these impossible again and again,

690
00:30:44,620 --> 00:30:48,540
 such as the story of Jesus feeding the 5,000.

691
00:30:48,540 --> 00:30:50,140
 You know, when Jesus wanted to feed the 5,000,

692
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:52,020
 he said, hey, why don't you guys go and feed them?

693
00:30:52,020 --> 00:30:54,060
 He told the disciples, you guys go and feed them.

694
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:55,700
 Disciples were like, what?

695
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:56,780
 No.

696
00:30:56,780 --> 00:30:57,980
 You know, if they say yes,

697
00:30:57,980 --> 00:31:00,940
 the story would have been the disciples fed the 5,000,

698
00:31:00,940 --> 00:31:02,980
 not Jesus fed the 5,000.

699
00:31:02,980 --> 00:31:04,980
 'Cause the original command was

700
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:06,980
 the disciples go to feed the 5,000.

701
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:09,740
 But you know, we're all like, oh, I can't do it,

702
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:10,820
 what do I have?

703
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:14,740
 In the same way, when Moses was leading

704
00:31:14,740 --> 00:31:16,380
 the Israelites out of Egypt,

705
00:31:16,380 --> 00:31:19,100
 they came to the Red Sea, and God was telling Moses,

706
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:21,660
 part of the Red Sea, Moses was like, what?

707
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:22,500
 Me?

708
00:31:22,500 --> 00:31:25,860
 But in all these stories, God asked them,

709
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:28,180
 or Jesus asked them always the same questions.

710
00:31:28,180 --> 00:31:29,300
 What do you have?

711
00:31:29,300 --> 00:31:31,980
 What do you have?

712
00:31:31,980 --> 00:31:33,740
 What do you have?

713
00:31:33,740 --> 00:31:34,860
 What do you have?

714
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:39,020
 The disciples brought forth a boy

715
00:31:39,020 --> 00:31:41,700
 with five loaves and two fish.

716
00:31:41,700 --> 00:31:43,340
 Moses says, I have a staff in my hand,

717
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:45,820
 and God says, use that, use whatever you have.

718
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:49,980
 So I just learned this yesterday.

719
00:31:49,980 --> 00:31:51,380
 I'm trying to live it out.

720
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:55,100
 So what I learned is, yes, when God's calling us

721
00:31:55,100 --> 00:31:59,700
 to do the impossible, the principle or the pattern is this,

722
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:03,580
 that we look at what we have,

723
00:32:03,580 --> 00:32:07,340
 we just go to do what we think we can do possibly,

724
00:32:07,340 --> 00:32:10,660
 and God will do the impossible in that process.

725
00:32:10,660 --> 00:32:13,580
 But here's the thing.

726
00:32:13,580 --> 00:32:16,660
 What do you have?

727
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:17,940
 What do we have?

728
00:32:17,940 --> 00:32:20,740
 You see, in this story, Peter said this,

729
00:32:20,740 --> 00:32:23,460
 like, you know, silver and gold, I do not have.

730
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:26,420
 I give you what I have, and so in Jesus' name,

731
00:32:26,420 --> 00:32:28,100
 come, stand up.

732
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:29,660
 I think now in this day and age,

733
00:32:29,660 --> 00:32:31,020
 we're quite like the opposite.

734
00:32:31,020 --> 00:32:32,980
 I have gold, I have silver, a little bit, not a lot,

735
00:32:32,980 --> 00:32:35,460
 just a little bit, tiny little bit,

736
00:32:35,460 --> 00:32:37,860
 especially after we have to pay for tuition,

737
00:32:37,860 --> 00:32:39,060
 tiny little bit.

738
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:43,620
 But I'm not sure if I have Jesus or not.

739
00:32:43,620 --> 00:32:44,460
 Well, don't get me wrong.

740
00:32:44,460 --> 00:32:46,380
 I have the knowledge of Jesus.

741
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:48,820
 I read the Bible a couple times.

742
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:50,700
 I have all this theology.

743
00:32:50,700 --> 00:32:54,660
 I have all this knowledge, like, you know, Wikipedia,

744
00:32:54,660 --> 00:32:58,500
 AI, Google, I've learned a lot of knowledge about Jesus.

745
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:03,500
 I know something, but do I have Jesus?

746
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:07,300
 Am I in this active relationship with him?

747
00:33:07,300 --> 00:33:10,580
 Am I in this intimacy with him that I know his heart,

748
00:33:10,580 --> 00:33:13,740
 that I walk in the fullness of his power every single day,

749
00:33:13,740 --> 00:33:15,940
 wherever I go, whether I'm in the office, at home,

750
00:33:15,940 --> 00:33:19,580
 or with someone else, am I like this?

751
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:21,420
 Am I in such a relationship with Jesus

752
00:33:21,420 --> 00:33:23,220
 that I can say the same words that Peter said?

753
00:33:23,220 --> 00:33:27,620
 I have Jesus, I'm gonna give you Jesus.

754
00:33:27,620 --> 00:33:29,860
 I think nowadays it's so much easier for us.

755
00:33:29,860 --> 00:33:31,500
 Okay, here is my gold and silver.

756
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,220
 I'll give you a tiny little bit.

757
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:34,580
 I'll share a bit with you.

758
00:33:34,580 --> 00:33:36,220
 I'll open my pocket.

759
00:33:36,220 --> 00:33:37,420
 That's still a Holy Spirit thing.

760
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:39,060
 Don't get me wrong, I'm not discouraging that.

761
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:42,100
 Please continue to give, you know, to give to the poor.

762
00:33:42,100 --> 00:33:43,940
 Continue, let's be generous.

763
00:33:43,940 --> 00:33:45,660
 That's correct.

764
00:33:45,660 --> 00:33:48,580
 But do we have Jesus to give to them?

765
00:33:48,580 --> 00:33:52,020
 God is calling us to do the impossible here in Yuen Long,

766
00:33:52,020 --> 00:33:53,260
 here in Hong Kong.

767
00:33:53,260 --> 00:33:56,180
 He's asking us, what do you have?

768
